That spans the full ML lifecycle — data versioning, experiment tracking, model registry, deployment, ML-specific monitoring (drift/decay), governance, and the growing LLMOps subset — plus the tool landscape for each stage. The highest-leverage starting stack for most teams is MLflow (tracking + registry) + DVC (data) + an orchestrator (Airflow/Kubeflow) + drift monitoring (Evidently), with KServe/BentoML for serving.